sources.title: High School Caesar
sources.description: Matt Stevens (John Ashley) is the big man at high school. He sweats the students for protection money, acquires copies of tests for a fee, and has rigged the votes so he can beat Kelly (Lowell Brown) in the election for student president. Aside from his anointed acolytes, Matt is almost universally despised. His parents are obscenely rich and spend their time travelling in Europe rather than giving him the parental guidance he needs. Things begin to get ugly when some of the teens resist his power and show Matt up at the drag race.

sources.title: High School Caesar (1960) JUVENILE DELINQUENTS
sources.description:
Stars: John Ashley, Gary Vinson, Judy Nugent
Writer/Director: O'Dale Ireland

A high school bully uses gangland tactics on his fellow students, but they eventual rebel and challenge him to a big drag race. Cool opening credits score.

sources.title: High School Caesar (1960) Drama Psychotronic Film
sources.description:
A small Midwestern school turns violent when an unscrupulous student uses gangland tactics on his classmates.

Director: O'Dale Ireland
Writers: O'Dale Ireland, Ethelmae Wilson Page 
Stars:  John Ashley, Gary Vinson, Steve Stevens
Genres: Drama, Psychotronic
